The paper deals with the problem of efficiently certifying upper bounds on the maximum value taken by a random tensor on the unit sphere, using the Sum of Squares (SoS) hierarchy. This involves techniques from computational complexity (cs.CC), information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and signal processing (cs.SI).
